<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363 Am 6/98: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-18T17:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 19—10:10
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>118. My August 12th, 10 a.m. British Minister insisting on immediate
                            convoking of Congress to special sessions in order that it may
                            reconsider its decision on Royal Bank matter, which he demands shall be
                            arbitrated.</p>
                        <pb facs="0790" n="666" xml:id="pg_666"/>
                        <p>President Acosta states Costa Rica will propose Chief Justice Taft as
                            arbitrator of both British claims.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>